amount to $420 million, representing an approximate 13% increase. The request for rate increase was driven by capital investments subsequent to
the previous base rate case, costs of complying with CCR regulations and the Coal Ash Act, costs relating to storm recovery, investments in customer
service technologies and recovery of costs associated with renewable purchased power.
