Impairment of Equity Method Investments
Duke Energy recorded OTTIs of the Constitution investment within Equity in earnings of unconsolidated affiliates on Duke Energy's Consolidated
Statements of Operations of $25 million and $55 million for the years ended December 31, 2019, and 2018, respectively. The current year charge
resulted in the full write-down of Duke Energy's investment in Constitution. The impairments were primarily due to the continued delay in resolving
project uncertainty through the courts and regulatory bodies, as well as recent pricing concerns between the customers and owners. For additional
information on the Constitution investment, see Note 4.
